product_name: NYX Professional MakeupThe Face Glue Gripping Setting Spray
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVeganGive BackGet glued with NYX Professional Makeup Face Glue Setting Spray! Locks in makeup for 24 hrs. Waterproof, transfer & fade-resistant, boosts color, with no sticky finish!
details: DetailsFeaturesDon't lock it down, GLUE down your makeup with The Face Glue Setting SprayThis makeup gripping, transfer-resistant setting spray seals in your look for up to 24 hours.Give it a good shake, and this Maple Syrup infused Setting Spray gives glue-level grip without the stick, boosting color vibrancy upon application!For optimal results, use in conjunction with The Face Glue Primer and The Brow Glue for a flawless, long-lasting makeup application.100% Cruelty free and vegan.Key IngredientsMaple Syrup keeps makeup gripped all day longItem 2626280How To UseFor makeup that's stuck like GLUE, shake well, and spray The Face Glue Setting Spray onto face from an arm's distance away after applying your full face of makeup.Pro Tip: Try The Face Glue Setting Spray as a primer spray and make a super glue sandwich with your full face routine!IngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Alcohol Denat., Propylene Glycol, PVP, Amp-Acrylates/Allyl Methacrylate Copolymer, Boron Nitride, Phenoxyethanol, Chlorphenesin, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Acer Saccharum Extract / Sugar Maple Extract.
how_to_use: For makeup that's stuck like GLUE, shake well, and spray The Face Glue Setting Spray onto face from an arm's distance away after applying your full face of makeup.Pro Tip: Try The Face Glue Setting Spray as a primer spray and make a super glue sandwich with your full face routine!
ingredients: Acer Saccharum Extract / Sugar Maple Extract

reviews.headline: Face Glue eats down!
reviews.comments: Tried the face glue primer and setting spray in 80 degree weather and my makeup has not moved. Also my pores look significantly diminished. The spray nozzle could be a bit more fine. Otherwise, I recommend and would use again.

reviews.headline: Perfect with some adjustments
reviews.comments: I can understand the mixed reviews for this product but its a packaging issue in my opinion. The nozzle is the worst. It's splatter-y and sprays too much at once. I swapped it with another fine mist spray nozzle from a diff drugstore brand I had empty and it was much better. I have extremely dry skin and hyperhydrosis so in the  summer I struggle to find a transfer proof spray that doesn't feel tight or dry or plasticy like it will crack right off(and has.) This doesn't have a tightening sensation when it dries down but it is long wearing and transferproof on me with a really nice finish and shine. You MUST shake it hard before spraying. Its not wet dewy its more of a lamination effect but it looks great. Recently wore it to a concert for hours, walked to and from the venue in 90 degree heat, and even danced the whole time and I still looked fresh at the end, which never happens.

reviews.headline: great product but not best for oily skin!
reviews.comments: I love the nyx brand & many of their products. This product is great for melting makeup into the skin & for layering. It does set makeup in place but the makeup will transfer (especially if you have oily skin). As someone with combination skin, I would recommend pairing it with a matte finishing spray.

reviews.comments: The setting spray got a grip feeling and I don't get as oily as much unlike some other setting sprays but after like 4 hours, my makeup starts to transfer. I can understand a small bit of transfer but for me, it was really bad which is a bummer.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I recently tried the NYX Face Glue Setting Spray, and it has quickly become a staple in my makeup routine. I wasn't sure what to expect at first, but after using it for a few weeks, I'm absolutely hooked. Here's my full review:

Packaging: The packaging is simple but effective. The spray nozzle disperses the product evenly and gives a fine mist, which prevents any splotchy spots or heavy droplets on my face. It's just the right amount of product each time, and I love how lightweight the bottle feels in my hand, making it easy to carry in my bag for on-the-go touch-ups.

Scent: The scent is quite subtle, which is a major plus for me since I'm sensitive to overpowering fragrances. It has a fresh, slightly floral scent that fades almost immediately after application, leaving behind no lingering smell. It's not chemically or artificial in any way, just a light, clean fragrance that doesn't interfere with my perfume or other products.

Texture & Finish: When it comes to texture, this setting spray is a game-changer. It's incredibly lightweight and feels almost like a fine mist of waterâ€”there's no sticky residue or heavy feeling after spraying it on my face. As for the finish, it's perfectly balanced. It doesn't leave my skin looking too matte or dewy but gives me a natural, fresh glow. The best part? It really locks in my makeup without making it look caked on or overdone. My foundation, concealer, and blush all stay in place for hours without fading, separating, or settling into fine lines. Even on long, busy days, my makeup still looks just as flawless as when I first applied it.

Coverage: While the setting spray doesn't offer coverage in terms of tint, it works wonders in enhancing the overall look and longevity of my makeup. It essentially "melts" all the products together, making my face look more cohesive and seamless. If you're worried about makeup looking too powdery or cakey, this spray is a lifesaver. It softens everything and gives a more natural, skin-like finish.

Performance: I've tried several setting sprays over the years, and this one really stands out. It does exactly what it promisesâ€”my makeup stays put all day, even in humid or slightly warmer conditions. I've tested it in different situations, from long days at work to nights out, and I've been seriously impressed with how my makeup looks at the end of the day. It controls shine without being overly drying, and my makeup doesn't budge, no matter what.

Overall, the NYX Face Glue Setting Spray is hands down one of the best setting sprays I've ever triedâ€”especially considering its price point. If you're looking for something that will keep your makeup intact all day, without feeling heavy or sticky, I'd highly recommend giving this a try. It truly delivers on its promise to lock in your makeup while giving you a fresh, natural finish.
faceoff_positive.headline: Awesome Setting Spray

faceoff_negative.comments: I didn't find this spray to be anything special or extraordinary. It's a typical, run of the mill setting spray. It does seem to separate quite easily though, and you can see what looks like a layer of white powder sitting on the bottom of the bottle when it's sat for a bitâ€¦which I suppose isn't a huge issueâ€¦but it takes an ungodly amount of shaking to get it to all mix back together. I'll stick to my MAC Fix+ or my Charlotte Tilbury sprays, that don't separate at all. My biggest issue with this product is the false marketing around this spray and the primer. NYX advertises that both products contain "maple syrup" in their advertising and product descriptionsâ€¦when neither product contains any maple syrup according to the ingredients. It DOES however list "sugar maple extract" in the ingredientsâ€¦and while both ingredients are derived from the same treeâ€¦they are NOT the same, and are VERY different in fact. I come from a family (myself included) who has produced maple syrup for generations, and I personally worked in the business side of the maple industry for almost 12 yearsâ€¦so the inaccurate advertising just annoys me. Do better NYXâ€¦
